#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
envkeep — a small, secure ENV-secret manager for a small team.

Architecture
------------
  * Source of truth : an age-encrypted `vault.age` living in a private git repo
                      (or any synced folder), encrypted to every teammate's
                      age public key listed in `recipients.txt`.
  * Local cache     : the macOS Keychain. `envkeep sync` decrypts the vault
                      into your login Keychain so reads are fast, local and
                      OS-protected (Touch ID / login gated).
  * CLI (this tool) : `envkeep get NAME` prints exactly one value — what a
                      coding session / Claude Code uses.
  * GUI             : `envkeep gui` opens a localhost web app for humans.

No pip dependencies. Requires: `age`, `age-keygen` (brew install age) and the
macOS `security` tool.
"""

